    • de.ovgu.softwareprojekt.examples.nes.SteeringWheel

    public class SteeringWheel
extends java.lang.Object
implements NetworkDataSink, AccelerationPhaseDetection.AccelerationListener
    Created by Ulrich on 12.12.2016 This class is responsible for steering the player in simple NES racing games

      • onData

        public void onData(NetworkDevice origin,
                   SensorData data,
                   float userSensitivity)
        onData is responsible for the controller input. SensorData send here is either gyroscope or accelerometer
        The gyroscope steers the player and is responsible for left right movement in the menu
        the accelerometer is responsible for throwing items and up, down movement in the menu
        Specified by:
        onData in interface NetworkDataSink
        Parameters:
        data - contains sensor data
        origin - where the sensor data comes from
        userSensitivity - the value set by the user. may be (as here) ignored when applying a custom sensitivity is too annoying.
